748.2003 (b)(5) Additional polies and procedures were created to ensure more oversight of the medication administration records ( MAR) Med carts and that items are checked and corrected regularly. Procedures were rolled out 02/03/21.
748.215(c) (3) Medication administration training was retaken by program staff. Corrective action was given to employees that were respo0nsible for ensuring medications were refilled timely and MARS were filled out correctly. 

Program assistant  will create a refill schedule for all received medications. This log will contain the childs name, name of medication, dosage, prescription number, date refill should be requested and date the last pill will administered. This schedule will be provided to the medical care coordinator and the program director. The program assistant will provide at a minimum, updates twice a week regarding the status of the refills and any follow up that may be needed. 
The medical care coordinator and supervisors will utilize the med carts checklist to ensure that all items regarding medication are accurately documented and immediately corrected. These will be noted on the checklist. Upon completion the checklist will be immediately scanned to all supervisors, program director and the medical care coordinator. 
"
