11/23/2020,748.2455(a)(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,01/13/2021,01/15/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Staff admitted they did not use techniques to de-escalate child prior to attempting EBI as staff stated they felt threatened. ,"01/15/21, email was provided by operation staff with the following compliance plan. 

Staff involved in this incident was immediately sent home after the allegations were made by the child. Staff was suspended the next morning pending the results of the investigation. Based on the results of the investigation, staff was terminated. Operation stated to ensure all discpline and EBI policies are followed all staff will be provided with additional training and coaching in this area. "
11/18/2020,748.3443(b)(2) - Physical Site,Physical Site,No,11/25/2020,11/25/2020,P:Physical Site,Medium,Yes,Walk-in freezer located in kitchen was at 8 degrees Fahrenheit as indicated by thermometer.,"The following Corrective Action Plan was developed in response to the inspection performed November 18, 2020, at St. Peter-St. Joseph Childrens Home Emergency Shelter, Operation # 817874:
 Outside play area had garbage such as plastic
bags, empty juice carton and paper on the ground
that was accessible to children.

Walk-in freezer located in kitchen was at 8 degrees 
Fahrenheit as indicated by thermometer

Four children's records read did not have reason
for medication being prescribed listed on
medication log


One child's medication record did not have
documented his PM medication given from the
previous evening.	11/18/2020	 Each item listed was immediately corrected prior to licensing leaving. 

All staff will attend medication administration training no later than 12/1/2020 in order to re-learn administration documentation processes.

Staff who did not sign out the medication, as well as the overnight staff who did not complete the mandatory check at shift change, received corrective action. 

Case management file audits will be increased to monthly from quarterly to ensure compliance. 

The Medical coordinator will move to daily documented MAR checks from weekly MAR checks to ensure compliance. 

The Medical Coordinator is a new staff and will be retrained on TDFPS minimum standards for medication. 

Walk in freezer temperature was elevated due to the cafeteria receiving a large order prior to licensing arriving. Temperature was at 0 degrees when licensing left, and a photo was sent to the licensing reps. 

 Trash on the playground was due to children having finished lunch. Staff will complete checks each shift to ensure no trash is accessible to children. 
"
